---
---

<section class="science" aria-labelledby="science-heading">
  <div class="science__inner">

    <div class="science__copy">
      <h2 class="science__heading" id="science-heading">
        This isn't a trend.<br />It's biology.
      </h2>
      <p class="science__body">
        Intermittent fasting triggers measurable metabolic changes —
        not theories, not influencer claims. After 12 hours without food,
        your body begins burning stored fat as its primary fuel.
      </p>
      <p class="science__body">
        After 16 hours, it enters peak fat-burning mode and begins
        autophagy — the cellular cleanup process recognized by the
        Nobel Prize in 2016.
      </p>
      <p class="science__body science__body--closer">
        FastMode shows you exactly when these thresholds happen.
        In real time. On your wrist.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="science__stats" aria-label="Key science figures">
      <div class="science__stats-row">
        <div class="science__stat">
          <span class="science__stat-value science__stat-value--green">3×</span>
          <span class="science__stat-label">more effective for fat loss than daily calorie restriction</span>
        </div>
        <div class="science__stat">
          <span class="science__stat-value science__stat-value--green">12h</span>
          <span class="science__stat-label">When fat burn begins</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="science__stats-row science__stats-row--bottom">
        <div class="science__stat">
          <span class="science__stat-value science__stat-value--orange">16h</span>
          <span class="science__stat-label">Peak fat burn &amp; autophagy kick in</span>
        </div>
        <div class="science__stat">
          <span class="science__stat-value science__stat-value--dark">Nobel<br />2016</span>
          <span class="science__stat-label">Autophagy research awarded Nobel Prize in Physiology</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="science__source">
      Source: Cell Metabolism, New England Journal of Medicine, and Obesity Reviews —
      peer-reviewed research on intermittent fasting and metabolic health.
    </p>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .science {
    padding: 48px 0;
  }

  .science__inner {
    max-width: var(--container-max);
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-inline: 24px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 8px;
  }

  .science__copy {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .science__heading {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 30px;
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .science__body {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  .science__body--closer {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }

  /* ── Stats grid ── */
  .science__stats {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .science__stats-row {
    display: flex;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .science__stats-row--bottom {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .science__stat {
    flex: 1;
    padding: 24px 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 8px;
  }

  .science__stat:first-child {
    padding-right: 20px;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .science__stat:last-child {
    padding-left: 20px;
  }

  .science__stat-value {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 48px;
    line-height: 0.95;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    display: block;
  }

  .science__stat-value--green  { color: var(--color-success); }
  .science__stat-value--orange { color: var(--color-primary); }
  .science__stat-value--dark   {
    font-size: 32px;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .science__stat-label {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 12px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    display: block;
  }

  /* ── Source ── */
  .science__source {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 12px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
    margin-top: 24px;
  }
</style>
